At phase boundary, the chemical potentials are equal:\mu(\alpha, p,T)=\mu(\beta, p, T)

where \alpha,\beta represent different phases

Consider the change in chemical potential during phase change \alpha\to\beta\begin{align*}

\mu(\beta, p,T) - \mu(\alpha, p,T)&= V_m(\beta)dp - S_m(\beta)dT-( V_m(\alpha)dp - S_m(\alpha)dT) \\
(V_m(\beta) - V_m(\alpha))dp &= (S_m(\beta) - S_m(\alpha))T \\

\end{align*}
